&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Accounts Assistant – Court of Protection&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ready to take your career to the next level?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Enable Law (part of the Foot Anstey Group) is one of the UK’s leading specialist medical negligence, personal injury, mental capacity and education law firms. Everything we do is about making life better for our clients and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The role in 60 seconds:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Accounts Assistant&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team&lt;/strong&gt;: Court of Protection&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt;: Plymouth &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working Pattern&lt;/strong&gt;: Full time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why this role matters&lt;/strong&gt;: This role plays a vital part in ensuring the smooth financial management of client matters within the Mental Capacity team. By maintaining accurate records, processing payments efficiently, and supporting key financial processes, you help safeguard client finances while enabling the wider team to deliver a high-quality, compliant service. Your attention to detail and collaborative approach directly contribute to building trust with clients and ensuring their financial affairs are managed with care and integrity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;________________________________________&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide support to the Unit Leader and wider Mental Capacity team on all client-related financial matters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process payments across the caseload in line with agreed terms, resolving any queries efficiently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with the preparation and submission of costing files to the Senior Courts Costs Office, liaising with costs draftsmen and the Court&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Carry out weekly bank reconciliations, ensuring accuracy and monitoring cash flow&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open and maintain client accounts as required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Undertake general administrative tasks, including completing forms, supplier correspondence, and data entry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure a high standard of service, quality, and compliance in line with firm policies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;____________________________________&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we’re looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of accounts processes and managing individual client budgets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High level of accuracy and attention to detail, particularly with numerical data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to prioritise workload effectively and build strong working relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organisational skills, with the ability to deliver high-quality work efficiently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in Microsoft Excel and Word&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proactive, flexible team player with a positive approach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills, with the ability to build and maintain client relationships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative mindset, working effectively across teams and practice areas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;_______________________________________&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What if I don’t tick every box?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re not box tickers. We appreciate the need for everyone to find a role that challenges them and gives them room for growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you bring transferable skills and a fresh perspective, we’d love to hear from you. If this role excites you and you have the skills to succeed, we encourage you to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
